			<h2>Why experience matters more, not less</h2>

			<p>The honest version. Junior developers using AI ship more code, but the same proportion of bad code as before. Sometimes more, because AI is fluent enough to bury the mistakes. Senior developers using AI ship better code faster, because they catch the errors AI can&#8217;t catch by definition: misalignments with the actual goal, subtle assumptions, the trade-off the prompt didn&#8217;t mention.</p>

			<p>That&#8217;s the offer. Senior practitioners with twenty years on the tools, using the best AI tools available, applied with the kind of judgement that only comes from having been wrong enough times to learn.</p>

		</div>

